race.comment: Most come out of the Leinster Cup. BOAB BOY (1) was backed off the map leading and winning a 64 by 10L and then the big money came again at Leinster where he was narrowly beaten from the front over this trip behind DANCING JACK. Has a 2kg claim and he will skip across and take plenty of pegging back. DANCING JACK (3) found more like his best winning that race by a nose. Well placed again with the 2kg claim and maps well. All things point to another bold run. GOT LUCKY (2) found the line nicely in the same race just nudged out. Good record at this journey and is one of the prime contenders. MONEY FOR OLD ROPE (7) was 2L adrift in that event and will be around the mark. HIS EMINENCE (4) brings different form lines and can't be ruled out.
